<subSubSection id="65DCBFD1BD29FF8C948F330672BEFA87" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="2D79EC5ABD29FF8C948F330672BEFA87" blockId="19.[113,1089,1140,1613]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C948F3306706BFB07" authority="Wollaston, 1854" authorityName="Wollaston" authorityYear="1854" box="[144,531,1140,1165]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C948F33067319FB06" box="[144,353,1142,1165]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Apion rotundipenne</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C95783304706BFB07" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[359,531,1140,1164]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" refId="ref13254" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1854: Insecta Maderensia: being an account of the insects of the Madeiran group. J. van Voorst, London, 634 pp." type="book" year="1854">Wollaston, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is here resurrected as a valid species, 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C97833306702AFB27" authority="(Wollaston, 1854)" baseAuthorityName="Wollaston" baseAuthorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Holotrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne" subGenus="Nesiapion">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C978333067638FB06" box="[924,1088,1142,1165]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Holotrichapion</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C946533E6729EFB26" box="[122,230,1174,1197]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Nesiapion</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C94E733E673FDFB26" box="[248,389,1174,1197]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">rotundipenne</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C958B33E47033FB27" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[404,587,1172,1196]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" refId="ref13254" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1854: Insecta Maderensia: being an account of the insects of the Madeiran group. J. van Voorst, London, 634 pp." type="book" year="1854">Wollaston, 1854</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This species is distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C978733E6705CFB47" authority="(Chevrolat, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Hemitrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni" subGenus="Lotapion">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C978733E67639FB26" box="[920,1089,1174,1197]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Hemitrichapion</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C946533C672A2FB46" box="[122,218,1206,1229]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Lotapion</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C94F433C67322FB46" box="[235,346,1206,1229]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">wollastoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C957633C47064FB47" author="CHEVROLAT A." box="[361,540,1204,1228]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="578 - 579" refId="ref12149" refString="CHEVROLAT A. 1852: Description de trois Coleopteres. Revue et Magasin de Zoologie, 2 me Serie 4: 578 - 579 [the second page of this paper is incorrectly paginated ' 279 ']." type="journal article" year="1852">Chevrolat, 1852</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The confusion over 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C971833C67296FB67" authority="(Wollaston)" baseAuthorityName="Wollaston" baseAuthorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Holotrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C971833C67638FB46" box="[775,1088,1206,1229]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Holotrichapion rotundipenne</emphasis>
(Wollaston)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C953B33A670BEFB67" authority="(Chevrolat)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[292,710,1236,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Hemitrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C953B33A6703CFB66" box="[292,580,1238,1261]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Hemitrichapion wollastoni</emphasis>
(Chevrolat)
</taxonomicName>
is discussed below under the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65DCBFD1BD29FF8B948F326571D5FDF8" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="2D79EC5ABD29FF8B948F326573F3FEF8" blockId="19.[113,1089,1140,1613]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1128,219,1095]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C948F3265732BFAA7" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[144,339,1300,1324]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" refId="ref13254" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1854: Insecta Maderensia: being an account of the insects of the Madeiran group. J. van Voorst, London, 634 pp." type="book" year="1854">WOLLASTON (1854</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C9542326473ECFAA7" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[349,404,1300,1324]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" refId="ref13354" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1865: Coleoptera Atlantidum, being an enumeration of the Coleopterous insects of the Madeiras, Salvages, and Canaries. J. van Voorst, London, 666 pp." type="book" year="1865">1865</bibRefCitation>
) included both 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C962432667177FAA6" box="[571,783,1302,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C962432667177FAA6" box="[571,783,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Apion rotundipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C975C32667290FAC7" authority="Chevrolat, 1852" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C975C32667180FAA6" box="[835,1016,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Apion wollastoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C97E032647290FAC7" author="CHEVROLAT A." pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="578 - 579" refId="ref12149" refString="CHEVROLAT A. 1852: Description de trois Coleopteres. Revue et Magasin de Zoologie, 2 me Serie 4: 578 - 579 [the second page of this paper is incorrectly paginated ' 279 ']." type="journal article" year="1852">Chevrolat, 1852</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. He had described 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C95B132467020FAC6" box="[430,600,1334,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C95B132467020FAC6" box="[430,600,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">A. rotundipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as new from Madeira (
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C975332447670FAC7" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[844,1032,1332,1356]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" refId="ref13254" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1854: Insecta Maderensia: being an account of the insects of the Madeiran group. J. van Voorst, London, 634 pp." type="book" year="1854">WOLLASTON 1854</bibRefCitation>
), and also gave an account of it in his first publication on Canarian 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C96E832247645FAE7" authority="(WOLLASTON 1864)" baseAuthorityName="WOLLASTON" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[759,1085,1364,1388]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">
Coleoptera (
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C97663224764EFAE7" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[889,1078,1364,1388]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" refId="ref13319" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1864: Catalogue of the Coleopterous insects of the Canaries in the collection of the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History), London, 648 pp." type="book" year="1864">WOLLASTON 1864</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequent authors, including 
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C95AF320570A7FA07" author="LINDBERG H. &amp; LINDBERG H." box="[432,735,1396,1420]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref12680" refString="LINDBERG H. &amp; LINDBERG H. 1958: Entomologische Ergebnisse der finnlandischen Kanaren-Expedition, 1947 - 51. No. 14. Coleoptera Insularum Canariensium. I. Aglycyderidae und Curculionidae. Commentationes Biologicae 17 (1): 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1958">LINDBERG &amp; LINDBERG (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, have used the name 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C97AA320672A2FA27" authority="Wollaston" authorityName="Wollaston" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C97AA32067638FA06" box="[949,1088,1398,1421]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">rotundipenne</emphasis>
Wollaston
</taxonomicName>
for this species and have not mentioned Chevrolat’s 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C96EC32E67103FA26" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1852" box="[755,891,1430,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C96EC32E67103FA26" box="[755,891,1430,1453]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">A. wollastoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as it is a Madeiran species). However, ALONSO- ZARAZAGA (1990a) formally synonymised the two names, with priority going to 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C953B32A673C8FA66" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1852" box="[292,432,1494,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C953B32A673C8FA66" box="[292,432,1494,1517]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">A. wollastoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This action was based on the identity of 
<specimenCount id="3BC027D3BD29FF8C977C32A57678FA67" box="[867,1024,1492,1516]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
in the Stockholm Museum (‘typus’ and ‘paratypus’), examined by Alonso-Zarazaga (and separately by myself) which purport to be the 
<typeStatus id="F27D52F8BD29FF8C95F131657064F9A6" box="[494,540,1557,1581]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C968031667154F9A6" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1852" box="[671,812,1558,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C968031667154F9A6" box="[671,812,1558,1581]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">A. wollastoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and are certainly conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD29FF8C94C4314673FDF9C6" box="[219,389,1590,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD29FF8C94C4314673FDF9C6" box="[219,389,1590,1613]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">A. rotundipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it is clear from 
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD29FF8C96813145711FF9C7" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[670,871,1588,1612]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" refId="ref13254" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1854: Insecta Maderensia: being an account of the insects of the Madeiran group. J. van Voorst, London, 634 pp." type="book" year="1854">WOLLASTON (1854)</bibRefCitation>
that his descriptions (in both English and Latin) and coloured plates refer, correctly, to two distinct species that are currently not even regarded as congeneric. The specimens purporting to be Chevrolat’s 
<typeStatus id="F27D52F8BD2EFF8B9488366C72BDFEBF" box="[151,197,284,308]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">type</typeStatus>
material are clearly anomalous, not agreeing with Chevrolat’s description, nor with the virtually contemporaneous ones of 
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD2EFF8B9612364C70A0FED8" author="WOLLASTON T. V." box="[525,728,315,339]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" refId="ref13254" refString="WOLLASTON T. V. 1854: Insecta Maderensia: being an account of the insects of the Madeiran group. J. van Voorst, London, 634 pp." type="book" year="1854">WOLLASTON (1854)</bibRefCitation>
, and clearly do not belong to the 
<typeStatus id="F27D52F8BD2EFF8B9026364C761FFEDF" box="[1081,1127,316,340]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B94E8362D73FCFEFF" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1852" box="[247,388,349,372]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B94E8362D73FCFEFF" box="[247,388,349,372]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">A. wollastoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D79EC5ABD2EFF8B94AA360B71F2FE78" blockId="20.[151,1128,219,1095]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">
Chevrolat’s description of 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B95C3360D7145FE18" authority="(CHEVROLAT 1852)" baseAuthorityName="CHEVROLAT" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[476,829,379,404]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B95C3360D7015FE1F" box="[476,621,381,404]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">A. wollastoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD2EFF8B9660360C714EFE18" author="CHEVROLAT A." box="[639,822,379,404]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" pagination="578 - 579" refId="ref12149" refString="CHEVROLAT A. 1852: Description de trois Coleopteres. Revue et Magasin de Zoologie, 2 me Serie 4: 578 - 579 [the second page of this paper is incorrectly paginated ' 279 ']." type="journal article" year="1852">CHEVROLAT 1852</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is reasonably detailed and includes characteristics which identify his species as a 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B96D436ED7190FE3F" authority="" box="[715,1000,412,436]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Hemitrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lotapion">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B96D436ED710AFE3F" box="[715,882,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">Hemitrichapion</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B979F36ED71A7FE3F" box="[896,991,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">Lotapion</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
as currently recognised. Additionally, specimens loaned from the Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Paris, proved instead to be specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B965436AD71FBFE7F" baseAuthorityName="Wollaston" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[587,899,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Holotrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B965436AD71FBFE7F" box="[587,899,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">Holotrichapion rotundipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D79EC5ABD2EFF8B94AA368C71D5FDF8" blockId="20.[151,1128,219,1095]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">
<bibRefCitation id="495791ABBD2EFF8B94AA368C73CAFD98" author="BRITO M. C. &amp; OROMI P." box="[181,434,507,532]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref12106" refString="BRITO M. C. &amp; OROMI P. 1986: Los Apionidos de las Islas Canarias (Coleoptera, Curculionoidea). Publicaciones Cientificas Excmo. Cabildo Insular de Tenerife. Museo Insular de Ciencias Naturales 1: 1 - 81." type="journal article" year="1986">BRITO &amp; OROMÍ (1986)</bibRefCitation>
recognised that 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B9672368D71E3FD98" authority="Chevrolat" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1852" box="[621,923,507,532]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B9672368D715FFD9F" box="[621,807,509,532]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">Apion wollastoni</emphasis>
Chevrolat
</taxonomicName>
was distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B9488356D733DFDBF" baseAuthorityName="Wollaston" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[151,325,541,564]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Holotrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B9488356D733DFDBF" box="[151,325,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">A. rotundipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It should be noted that, presumably because of erroneous pagination in Chevrolat’s account, WOLLASTON’ S (1854, 1865) references to the description of 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B97C3354D761FFDDF" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1852" box="[988,1127,573,596]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollastoni">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B97C3354D761FFDDF" box="[988,1127,573,596]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">A. wollastoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are incorrect; the correct citation is given in the References section below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65DCBFD1BD2EFF8B94AA350D73A2FBCC" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D79EC5ABD2EFF8B94AA350D7347FD58" blockId="20.[151,1128,219,1095]" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B94AA350D7394FD1F" baseAuthorityName="Wollaston" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[181,492,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Holotrichapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipenne">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B94AA350D7394FD1F" box="[181,492,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">Holotrichapion rotundipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very common species throughout the western islands (in all of which I have recorded it), in association with species of 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B972A35ED7113FD3F" box="[821,875,669,692]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B972A35ED7113FD3F" box="[821,875,669,692]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">Vicia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B976535ED71A1FD3F" box="[890,985,669,692]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lathyrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1FB23048BD2EFF8B976535ED71A1FD3F" box="[890,985,669,692]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="177">Lathyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and possibly other 
<taxonomicName id="EAC697D9BD2EFF8B94CA35CB7344FD58" box="[213,316,699,723]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="20" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
